job.description:
Required Skills:  - Expert in MySQL and one or more of the following: Oracle, Mongodb, Postgres, Oracle, MSSQL, Kafka, Hadoop, Hbase or Hive&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience in Kafka for at least 1 year is Must.    
  - Bachelor's degree in computer science or Information Technology   
  - Expert in database and SQL tuning&amp;nbsp;   
  - Expert trouble-shooter&amp;nbsp;   
  - Authored software to do parts or all of your job   
  - Strong Shell, Python and SQL scripting to automate DB related jobs&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with observability tools such as Grafana, Prometheus, Vividcortex, Solarwinds, Nagios, Icinga, Munin, Cacti, Wireshark   
  - Ability to work with development teams&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with low level debugging tools: strace, tcpdump, gdb, lsof and netstat&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with Splunk&amp;nbsp;   
  - Expertise in setting up and testing backups&amp;nbsp;   
&amp;nbsp;Responsibilities:  - Respond to issues within the Service Level Objective during your assigned on-call rotation   
  - Support 1 of 2 of these tracks of technology   
  - Kafka, ElasticSearch+LogStash+Kibana and RabbitMQ   
  - MySQL, Postgres, Oracle, MSSQL   
  - Write software to improve the reliability, scalability and performance of Client’s infrastructure   
  - Troubleshoot broken systems and services issues
